############################################################################### 
                Raptor, A Rapid Silicon complete Software solution 
                            Installation Help
###############################################################################

Print this Help message:

    ./Raptor_x.x.run --help

=> Make sure to provide empty directory for the installation as installer wipe the directory before doing installation 

GUI Mode:>
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
1): With SUDO/Admin privileges, say yes to dependencies installation and default path when installer prompt for questions. 

        sudo ./Raptor_x.x.run 

2): Without SUDO/Admin privileges, say no to dependencies installation and choose custom writeable path when installer prompt for questions

                    ./Raptor_x.x.run 

Batch Mode (No GUI):>
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
1): Do not install OS related dependencies and install Raptor at desired path, then execute the installer with command 

            ./Raptor_x.x.run  --batch --accept --no-dep-install -r <absolute path where Raptor will be installed>

This assume that all OS dependencies of Raptor are already installed. 

2): Do not install OS related dependencies and Raptor at pre-defined path, then execute with SUDO/Admin privileges

          sudo ./Raptor_x.x.run --batch --accept --no-dep-install -r /opt/raptor

2): To install OS related dependencies and Raptor at pre-defined path, then execute with SUDO/Admin privileges

          sudo ./Raptor_x.x.run --batch --accept --install-dep -r /opt/raptor

NOTE:> For details of command line options and license setup, see the README.md
^^^^